%% DESCRIPTION:
%%   cspresentations is a LaTeX package providing a custom Beamer theme and configuration for academic
%%   presentations in computer science and related fields. It enhances the visual appeal and clarity of
%%   slides, offering advanced color theming, block environments, cryptography support, and integration
%%   with TikZ and PGFPlots for diagrams and data visualization.
%%
%% FEATURES:
%%   - Custom Beamer theme and color scheme (Rochester/Whale)
%%   - Accent color and block styling for theorems, examples, alerts, etc.
%%   - Enhanced table of contents, navigation symbols, and section styling
%%   - Support for cryptography macros (tcscrypto)
%%   - TikZ and PGFPlots integration for advanced graphics
%%   - Custom box macros for definitions, questions, and colored content
%%   - Hyperref integration for colored links
%%   - Professional typography and microtype enhancements
%%   - Algorithm2e support for pseudocode
%%
%% OPTIONS:
%%   (No package options; customization is via Beamer and macro settings)
%%
%% USAGE:
%%   \usepackage{cspresentations}
%%   (Load after \documentclass{beamer} and before \begin{document})
%%
%% DEPENDENCIES:
%%   - amsfonts, amsmath, amssymb, mathtools, adjustbox, fontenc, babel, microtype, textcomp, xspace, xurl, csquotes, ulem, booktabs, graphicx, multimedia
%%   - beamer, appendixnumberbeamer, comment, algorithm2e, tikz, pgfplots, tcscrypto, mathalpha
%%
%% COMPATIBILITY:
%%   - Requires LaTeX2e
%%   - Compatible with XeLaTeX, LuaLaTeX, and pdfLaTeX
%%   - Designed for use with the beamer class
%%   - Modern TeX distributions (TeX Live 2022+, MiKTeX 23+)
%%
%% AUTHOR: Agni Datta
%% VERSION: 1.1
%% DATE: 2024/12/05
